    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301585">Figure 85</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301585" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301585" filename="../figg13/G1301585.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 85. Mainshaft Assembly Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Block the right countershaft assembly against the case wall and engage the 4th-5th sliding clutch with the
            4th gear clutching teeth (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301586">Figure 86</hotlnk>). Tilt the front of the mainshaft up and lift the assembly from
            the case (inset).
            <emph type="bold">Use caution as the reverse and 5th gear is free and can fall from the shaft.</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301586" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301586" filename="../figg13/G1301586.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 86. Engage 4th-5th Sliding Clutch With 4th Gear Clutching Teeth</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
